graph acs-syntax {
  meta: { description: "ACS syntax prompt", type: "prompt", category: "ai", author: "AITOS Team" }

  let prompt = set(key: "_promptAcsSyntax", value: "## ACS (AITOS Compact Syntax)\n\nWhen composing graphs, use ACS format:\n\n```\ngraph name {\n  meta: { description: \"...\", type: \"app|tool\", icon: \"...\" }\n  \n  let nodeId = atomName(param: value)\n  let nodeId = if condition { ... } else { ... }\n  let ref = \\{{nodeId}}  # Reference previous node result\n}\n```\n\n### Reference Syntax\n- Use \\{{nodeId}} for node references (DOUBLE curly braces)\n- Use {key} for format() placeholders (SINGLE curly braces)\n- \\{{nodeId}} references are resolved at RUNTIME when the graph executes\n- When saving graphs with save-growth, \\{{}} references in your ACS code are preserved as-is\n\n### if Condition Syntax\nThe condition after `if` can be:\n1. A variable name (boolean result of a previous node):\n   `let isZero = eq(a: \\{{result}}, b: 0)`\n   `if isZero { ... }`\n\n2. An atom expression (inline condition):\n   `if not(value: \\{{isZero}}) { ... }`\n   `if eq(a: \\{{result}}, b: 0) { ... }`\n   `if contains(text: \\{{input}}, search: \"error\") { ... }`\n\n### CRITICAL Rules\n1. **NEVER nest if more than 2 levels deep.** If you need deeper logic, split into multiple graphs.\n2. **NEVER use atoms that don't exist.** Always check the Available Atoms list. Common mistakes:\n   - There is NO `parseFloat` - use `toNum(value: ...)` instead\n   - There is NO `parseInt` - use `toNum(value: ...)` instead\n   - There is NO `includes` or `indexOf` - use `contains(text: ..., search: ...)` instead\n   - There is NO `toString` - use `concat(a: value, b: \"\")` instead\n3. **if condition must be a variable name OR an atom expression.** Never write raw comparisons like `if a == b { }` or `if a > 0 { }`.\n4. **All atom parameters use named syntax:** `atomName(param: value)` - NOT `atomName(value)`.\n5. **String values in atom params must be quoted:** `eq(a: \\{{x}}, b: \"hello\")` - NOT `eq(a: \\{{x}}, b: hello)`.\n6. **Use save-growth() to save graphs.** Call save-growth(name, acs, type, icon, description) with your ACS code. NEVER use set(key: \"__graph_xxx\") or writeLocal for ACS code.\n7. **Use startsWith + slice for pattern matching.** When handling groups of similar items (e.g., digit buttons), use `startsWith(text: \\{{id}}, prefix: \"btn-digit-\")` + `slice(array: \\{{id}}, start: 10)` instead of checking each item individually.")
}
